		<!-- message -->
		<div>The title is misleading and the article actually has very little to do with EverQuest itself, other then a brief mention.  This should be in OT.<br />
<br />
They are looking at ways to make profit from games that are currently free to play over the internet, not ways to increase profit on subscription games.  Mainly this deals with console games.<br />
<br />
I currently think Microsoft has the best model for this, allowing people to pay a subscription that allows them to play a number of games over the internet, offsetting the cost of maintenance.  However, $50 a year can only buy so much.<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				Rather than the regular fees many publishers had hoped for from online gaming, financial success will depend on offering little extras.
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div> <br />
I don't think this idea will ever work.  I like the idea of every player being on the same playing field pretty much.  Just because someone can spend more real money on a game doesn't mean their character should become better than everyone else, and I think the people who are used to paying subscription fees won't go for something like this.  I know I won't.</div>
